  "body": "Currently I have a task that allows me to pull the constructor & address, but not the networks. Which would be handy to verify multiple chains. \r\n\r\nIs there anyway to input the chains name into the task instead of the terminal?\r\n\r\n```npx hardhat verify --network bscTestnet```\r\n\r\nLets say I want to do \r\n\r\n``` npx hardhat verify --network bscTestnet mumbai fantomTestnet```\r\n\r\nOr\r\n\r\n``` npx hardhat verify --network chains```\r\n\r\nWhere chains was an array or chains.\r\n\r\n\r\nBut to do more then one chain on a loop, there is no `network` key in the object or array that you look for in the verification script. \r\n",
